Katas — Programming Exercises
==============================

A collection of small programming challenges written in PHP.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Kata1 — PI Number
Displays digits of PI one by one each time a key is pressed.

Kata2 — Postal Order
Simulates a post office queue system with turn types (C, E, R, O, I) and consecutive numbering per type.

Kata3 — Sant Jordi
Randomly gives you a book or a rose as a gift, with 5 possible options for each.

Kata4 — Lights Out
4x4 grid puzzle inspired by the PSX game Alundra. Stepping on a tile toggles its 4 neighbor tiles.

Kata5 — Lights Out 2
Continuation of Kata4. Grid state persists between moves and the game ends when all tiles match.

Kata6 — Letter T
Given a number n, prints the letter T using characters. The top row is n horizontal and a vertical path that goes down the center.

Kata7 — Match Up ER Diagram
ER diagram for a card-matching game. Models users, games, cards, and card details.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

To run any kata: "php YourFileDirectory/FileName.php" on the terminal.
